The Dirk <br/>
<br/>
Average Length: Approx. up to 20 inches<br/>
<br/>
Type of Weapon: Distanced Hand-to-hand.<br/>
<br/>
Commonly used by: thiefs <br/>
<br/>
The dirk was characteristically, almost exclusively, a Scottish dagger<br/>
weapon. It had a long thin blade, usually sharpened only on one edge,<br/>
a conical hilt adorned with studs, and often an engraved blade. Dirks<br/>
were used favored by thiefs as there were easily concealed. 		<br/>
